MongoDB Lab Assignment
Objective:
To perform basic MongoDB operations using MongoDB Compass CLI.

Step 1: Open MongoDB Compass CLI
1. Open MongoDB Compass
2. Connect to mongodb://localhost:27017
3. Open Mongosh CLI
4. Use the database:

use college
Step 2: Insert Records
a) Insert one record

db.students.insertOne({
  roll: 41,
  name: "Soham",
  department: "computer",
  year: 2
})

b) Insert multiple records

db.students.insertMany([
  { roll: 2, name: "Rahul", department: "computer", year: 1 },
  { roll: 3, name: "Sneha", department: "electronics", year: 3 },
  { roll: 4, name: "Puja", department: "computer", year: 2 },
  { roll: 5, name: "Arjun", department: "mechanical", year: 4 }
])

Step 3: Delete the First Record

db.students.deleteOne({ roll: 1 })

Step 4: Query Computer Department Students

db.students.find({ department: "computer" }).pretty()

Step 5: Update Department Name

db.students.updateMany(
  { department: "computer" },
  { $set: { department: "BCA" } }
)

Final Verification

db.students.find().pretty()


